vim

Description:
Delete text

x   -> delete (cut) character
dw  -> delete (cut) the characters of the word from the
      cursor position to the start of the next word
de  -> delete (cut) the characters of the word from the
      cursor position to the end the current word
d$  -> delete (cut) to the end of the line
db  -> delete back to the beginning of the word
dd  -> delete (cut) a line
dh  -> delete one left character
dj  -> delete current line and one down line
dk  -> delete current line and one up line
dl  -> delete one right character
d6w -> Execute command dw 6 times